// Go workspace for in-repo development across zeroid's three published
// modules. When you run `go build` or `go test` from anywhere inside the
// repo, Go reads this file and treats the three modules as one workspace
// — local code in ./pkg/authjwt and ./pkg/dpop is used directly,
// regardless of what versions zeroid/go.mod's require directives
// declare. This lets zeroid/go.mod reference real published subpackage
// versions (required for downstream `go get` resolution) without
// breaking the in-repo dev loop.
//
// pkg/authjwt is also covered by a `replace ./pkg/authjwt` directive in
// zeroid/go.mod. That replace is redundant with this workspace for the
// common dev path, but keeps `GOWORK=off` builds working (some CI
// matrix variants disable workspace mode). pkg/dpop has no such
// replace — its version reference in zeroid/go.mod is a real
// published version (decoupled release cadence via release-dpop.yml).
//
// Releases: see RELEASING.md. Normal zeroid release is just "click
// Publish in UI" — no version-bumping ceremony required because
// zeroid/go.mod pins pkg/dpop to a specific released version that
// stays static across most zeroid releases.

go 1.26.0

use (
	.
	./pkg/authjwt
	./pkg/dpop
)
